import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='net_generation', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend in net generation of electricity over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby(['source'])['net_generation'].sum().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='source', y='net_generation', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['net_generation'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['net_generation'].max():.2f}")
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('Which energy source has the highest net generation of electricity?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    sns.scatterplot(x='year', y='net_generation', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between net generation of electricity and year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['net_generation'] = pd.to_numeric(data['net_generation'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='net_generation', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['net_generation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['net_generation'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of net generation of electricity?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
